• Restates commitment to blocking revenue leakages The Federal Operations Unit (FOU) of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS), said it generated about N19 billion into the Government’s coffers in the last nine months, even as it reiterated commitment to blocking revenue leakages and combating smuggling.  He, however, warned smugglers to desist from sabotaging the nation’s economy through their nefarious activities.
 
“We shall remain firm and resolute in discharging our duties in accordance with the extant laws without fears or intimidation. Support and facilitate legitimate compliant traders to succeed in their businesses. While we continue to thank our esteemed stakeholders and patriotic citizens for their unflinching support, we solicit for useful and timely information to serve our nation better,” he stated. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .